</ref>。

自山脚至山顶有诸多[[生物群系|植被带]]<ref name=kirinyaga>{{cite book
|title= Kirinyaga: a fable of Utopia
|last= Resnick
|first= Mike
|authorlink= Mike Resnick
|year= 1998
|publisher= Ballantine
|location=
|isbn= 0-345-41701-1
|page= [https://archive.org/details/kirinyagafableof00resn/page/293 293]
|url=https://archive.org/details/kirinyagafableof00resn
|accessdate= }}
</ref>，山坡下部由多种树林覆盖。诸多高山植物为肯尼亚[[特有种|特有]]，如巨型[[半边莲属|半边莲]]、[[黄菀属|黄菀]]及当地亚种[[蹄兔|蹄兔]]<ref name=ecology>{{cite book
| last=Coe | first=Malcolm James
| title=The Ecology of the Alpine Zone of Mount Kenya
| url=https://archive.org/details/ecologyofalpinez0017coem | year=1967 | publisher= Dr W. Junk | location=The Hague}}</ref>。肯尼亚山中部面积{{convert|715|km2|sqmi}}的地区被指定为[[肯尼亚山国家公园|国家公园]]<ref name=uicn>{{cite web
|url=http://whc.unesco.org/archive/advisory_body_evaluation/800.pdf
|title=World Heritage Nomination – IUCN Technical Evaluation Mount Kenya (Kenya)
|accessdate=2016-08-31
|archive-date=2011-09-19
|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110919022347/http://whc.unesco.org/archive/advisory_body_evaluation/800.pdf
|dead-url=no
}}</ref>，于1997年成为[[世界遗产|联合国教科文组织世界遗产]]<ref name=unesco>{{cite web
 |url         = http://whc.unesco.org/pg.cfm?cid=31&id_site=800
 |title       = Mount Kenya National Park/Natural Forest
 |accessdate  = 23 February 2008
 |author      = United Nations
 |authorlink  = United Nations
 |year        = 2008
 |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20061230202343/http://whc.unesco.org/pg.cfm?cid=31&id_site=800
 |archivedate = 2006年12月30日
 |deadurl     = yes
}}</ref>。国家公园每年访客量超过16,000人<ref name=development/>。

